As the number of Covid-19 infections continues to soar in the country, researchers from the Kenya Medical Research Institute, KEMRI have detected a new variant of Covid 19 from samples collected in Tigoni Kiambu County. KEMRI says 7 out of the 15 samples tested positive for the variant of concern Delta variant and that continuous surveillance of covid 19 has established that three global variants of concern including the delta variant, are now the dominant sources of covid-19 cases in the country.
